		"title": "USN-3839-1 -- WavPack vulnerabilities",
		"description": "It was discovered that WavPack incorrectly handled certain WAV files. An attacker could possibly use this issue to cause a denial of service. (CVE-2018-19840, CVE-2018-19841)  Update Instructions:  Run `sudo pro fix USN-3839-1` to fix the vulnerability. The problem can be corrected by updating your system to the following package versions:  libwavpack1 - 4.75.2-2ubuntu0.2 libwavpack-dev - 4.75.2-2ubuntu0.2 wavpack - 4.75.2-2ubuntu0.2 No subscription required",
